{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | color = | name = ''Deferribacter autotrophicus'' | domain = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Deferribacteres]]
| classis = [[Deferribacteres]]
| ordo = [[Deferribacterales]]
| familia = [[Deferribacteraceae]] | genus = ''[[Deferribacter]]'' | species = '''''D. autotrophicus''''' | binomial = ''Deferribacter autotrophicus'' | binomial_authority = Slobodkina et al. 2009 }}
'''''Deferribacter autotrophicus''''' is an [[iron]]-reducing bacteria. It is [[thermophilic]], anaerobic, [[chemolithoautotrophic]], [[motile]], straight to bent rod-shaped with one polar [[flagellum]], 0.5–0.6 [[micrometre|µm]] in width and 3.0–3.5&nbsp;µm in length. The type strain is SL50<sup>T</sup> (=DSM 21529<sup>T</sup> =VKPM B-10097<sup>T</sup>).<ref name="SlobodkinaKolganova2009">{{cite journal|last1=Slobodkina|first1=G. B.|last2=Kolganova|first2=T. V.|last3=Chernyh|first3=N. A.|last4=Querellou|first4=J.|last5=Bonch-Osmolovskaya|first5=E. A.|last6=Slobodkin|first6=A. I.|title=Deferribacter autotrophicus sp. nov., an iron(III)-reducing bacterium from a deep-sea hydrothermal vent|journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology|volume=59|issue=6|year=2009|pages=1508–1512|issn=1466-5026|doi=10.1099/ijs.0.006767-0|pmid=19502344}}</ref>
