'''[[Samsung]]''' has a long history of designing and producing [[system on chip|systems on chip]] (SoCs) and has been manufacturing SoCs for its own devices as well as for sale to other manufacturers. The first Samsung SoC, the ''S3C44B0'', was built around an [[ARM7]] CPU which operated at 66&nbsp;[[Hertz|MHz]] clock frequency. Later, several SoCs (S3C2xxx) containing an [[ARM9]] CPU were produced.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.samsung.com/global/business/semiconductor/product/application/catalogue?iaId=836 |title=Application Processor Product Catalogue &#124; Samsung Semiconductor Global Website |publisher=Samsung.com |accessdate=2012-10-02}}</ref> For more information on Samsung's current SoCs see [[Exynos]].
