{{Infobox book | name = Wonders of the Universe | image = Wonders of the Universe (book).jpg| caption = | author = [[Brian Cox (physicist)|Brian Cox]], Andrew Cohen | language = English | genre = [[Non-fiction]] | subject = [[Physics]], [[cosmology]], [[universe]] | country = | publisher = Collins | pub_date = 2011 | pages = 256 pp. | isbn = 9780007395828 | preceded_by = [[Wonders of the Solar System (book)|Wonders of the Solar System]] | followed_by = [[The Quantum Universe]] }} '''''Wonders of the Universe''''' is a 2011 book by the [[Theoretical physics|theoretical physicists]] [[Brian Cox (physicist)|Brian Cox]] and Andrew Cohen. The book is about [[cosmology]] and [[Universe|the universe]], and is explained in a way that is accessible to a general reader. The book is based on a series with the same name ''[[Wonders of the Universe]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Digested read: Wonders of the Universe by Brian Cox|url = https://www.theguardian.com/books/2011/mar/21/wonders-of-the-universe-cox|website = the Guardian|accessdate = 2015-11-21|first = John|last = Crace}}</ref>
